The paper discusses a method for machine learning tasks using Genetic Programming (GP) and focuses on transforming the representation of a large-scale machine learning dataset into a more compact representation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the development of an autoencoder, which is a common technique used in deep learning, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also tests its approach on image datasets, suggesting that it may belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Furthermore, the use of evolutionary algorithms in machine learning tasks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) or Systems and Control (cs.SY).
